messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /api/users/{id}

- All methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the user router at app.use('/api/users', userRoutes), so paths defined in routes/userRoutes.js are prefixed with /api/users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the route for '/:id' registers handlers for .delete(protect, admin, deleteUser), .get(protect, admin, getUserById) and .put(protect, admin, updateUser). That makes GET, PUT and DELETE explicitly acceptable for the full path /api/users/:id (represented above as /api/users/{id}).
- There is no router.all or other catch-all that would make "all methods" acceptable, so "All methods acceptable" is false.
- HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PATCH are not explicitly registered for this route in the code, so they are reported as not acceptable. (Note: Express automatically provides HEAD responses for GET in many setups, but per your instruction the determination is based only on the code, not on runtime/Framework behavior assumptions.)
